Name: Eliminate All Corrupted Around Oasis
Content: As the number of the Corrupted on Earth has been rising, so too has the number of refugees flocking to the base of the Forsaken. Due to insufficient soldiers there, Babylonia has received a request to eliminate the Corrupted around the Oasis base.

Name: Abnormal Situation Reconnaissance
Content: Abnormalities have been detected on Earth, presumably associated with the Corrupted. Assistance is requested for the recon operation.

Name: Rescue Operation on Earth
Content: The invasion of the Corrupted has caused quite a number of casualties. Reinforcements are requested for immediate aid.

Name: Provisions Transportation
Content: A batch of provisions is to be transported from Babylonia to a conservation area on Earth. Constructs experienced in piloting are requested to escort the transportation.

Name: Emergency Maintenance
Content: Power deficiency has been detected in Babylonia's Weather Engine Group B. Deployment of Constructs for cooperative maintenance is requested.

Name: Ancient Ruins Expedition
Content: New ancient ruins have been discovered on Earth. Constructs are requested to take on an investigation into the ruins.

Name: Diplomatic Negotiation
Content: A new season of goods trade has kicked off. This time, Babylonia will be sitting at the negotiation table with Kowloong. Constructs with exceptional bargaining skills are requested to help the two parties reach an ideal reciprocal agreement.

Name: Fend Off Raging Corrupted
Content: The Arctic Route Union is under savage attack from the Corrupted. Babylonia is requested to deploy Constructs for reinforcements.

Name: New Ancient Ruins Discovered
Content: It appears that new ancient ruins have been discovered on Earth. Assistance is requested for a cooperative investigation. Once its danger level has been identified, the WGAA will lay out a follow-up operation.

Name: Rescue Request From Oasis
Content: Because of a lack of manpower in the Oasis base, the invasion of the Hetero-Creatures has caused severe casualties. Timely aid is requested before casualties further increase.

Name: Valuables Transportation
Content: The WGAA has again unearthed a batch of cultural and artistic artifacts. Constructs are requested to escort the transportation of these valuables back to Babylonia.

Name: Central Purification Filter Emergency Maintenance
Content: The concentration of the Punishing Virus in a conservation area is gradually increasing due to a malfunction in the Central Purification Filter. Assistance is requested to repair the Central Purification Filter.

Name: Explore the Kowloong Ruins
Content: After wiping out a horde of Corrupted, new Koloong ruins were discovered inland. Babylonia is requested to deploy Constructs for a cooperative investigation into the ruins.

Name: Negotiation With Scavengers
Content: A group of Scavengers has occupied a small base on the outskirts of the Oasis. Due to a manpower shortage, the Forsaken have requested Constructs with outstanding bargaining skills from Babylonia to talk this out with Scavengers.

Name: Eliminate the Corrupted for Asslam
Content: A station along Asslam's railway has been occupied by the Corrupted. As it will impose potential risks on the transportation, Babylonia is requested to deploy Constructs to eliminate all the Corrupted there.

Name: Reconnaissance of New City
Content: Babylonia has discovered a new city on Earth. Constructs are requested to identify the location details of its Central Purification Filter and assess its danger level there.

Name: Medical Assistance Request
Content: The invasion of the Corrupted has nearly exhausted the medical materials in the conservation area. Immediate medical assistance is requested.

Name: Goods Trade With Akdilek
Content: The goods that the Kowloong Corp ordered are ready for transportation. However, given the considerable distance between Akdilek and Kowloong, Babylonia is requested, with rewards offered, to deploy escorts for the transportation.

Name: Simulation Hall Malfunctions
Content: The scene-switch function in the simulation hall is currently not operating normally. Constructs are requested to investigate and join the cooperative maintenance.

Name: Research Center Ruins Expedition
Content: A site of ruins from a Golden Age research center was discovered near a conservation area. Constructs are requested by the Science Council for an investigation into the ruins.

Name: Archives Management
Content: The military is currently reorganizing its archives from the last few years. Constructs experienced in handling confidential information are requested for assistance.

Name: Retrieval of Lost Materials
Content: The Engineering Force lost a batch of materials due to an assault from the Corrupted. Reinforcements are requested to eliminate the Corrupted and retrieve the materials.

Name: Conservation Area Routine Patrol
Content: As certain guards from the conservation area are reassigned to other missions, assistance is requested for the routine patrols.

Name: Combat Medical Assistance
Content: A combat has erupted in a city on Earth. Medical assistance is requested for the wounded.

Name: Transportation of the Forsaken's Materials
Content: A batch of medical materials has to be transported to a base. However, Due to a manpower shortage, the Forsaken have requested escorts, with rewards offered.

Name: Conservation Area Routine Maintenance
Content: The Engineering Force has requested assistance in the routine maintenance of the Central Purification Filter and other facilities in a conservation area.

Name: Exploration Assistance
Content: Due to interference from the Corrupted, the exploration of the ruins is falling behind schedule. Assistance is requested for the remaining exploration work.

Name: Archives Management
Content: The Star of Life is currently recategorizing its archives from the last few years. Considering their highly confidential nature, external personnel involvement is not allowed. Therefore, Constructs are requested by the Star of Life for assistance.

Name: Reinforcements to Conservation Area
Content: Urgent: The invasion of the Corrupted has reached the interior of a conservation area. Attacker-type Constructs are requested for immediate reinforcements.

Name: Data Collection Assistance
Content: The Science Council has received a report from a city on Earth about certain abnormal behaviors of the Hetero-Creatures. It is possible that data can be collected onsite. Assistance is requested.

Name: Combat Commission
Content: The facilities around the Arctic Route Union were raided by the Hetero-Creatures. There have also been reports of missing persons. Babylonia is requested to deploy Constructs for reinforcements and to search for the missing persons.

Name: Combat Medical Request
Content: A combat has erupted in a city on Earth. Combatants and medics are requested for urgent response.

Name: Abnormality in the Naval Route
Content: An abnormality, presumably the flying Hetero-Creatures, has been detected in the navigation route to the Kowloong port. The number of creatures does not seem to be a significant threat, but caution is required. Babylonia is requested to clear the route.

Name: Eliminate the Corrupted in Ruins
Content: With the exploration completed, the WGAA has confirmed the age of the ruins. Threat elimination will soon commence.\nAs the Corrupted have already been detected within the ruins, deploying Constructs with great combat abilities is recommended.

Name: Combat First Aid Guidance
Content: The Star of Life has recruited a number of fresh graduates and soldiers. Constructs with combat experiences are requested to provide combat first aid guidance for them.

Name: Abnormality on the Surface
Content: An abnormality, presumably the Hetero-Creatures, has been detected in a city on Earth. Reinforcements are requested for reconnaissance.\nNote: Casualties have been reported.

Name: Research Center's Facility Maintenance
Content: The Science Council has been receiving abnormal data recently. It is presumed that the facilities on Earth are afflicted with malfunctions. Babylonia is requested to deploy Constructs for assistance in locating data sources and repairing and upgrading the facilities.

Name: Ruins Abnormality Reconnaissance
Content: A report about a raid from the Corrupted on the ruins has been received. Although the Corrupted have already been driven out, certain persons are being trapped in the ruins, and parts of the excavation site have been reburied. Medical materials are sufficient there. Babylonia is requested to deploy Constructs for reconnaissance and exploration work.

Name: Reconnaissance Assistance
Content: Defecting Constructs have been reported to appear near a Scavenger's base. As the reconnaissance will need cooperation with the Scavengers, Constructs with great negotiation skills are also requested to come along.

Name: Medical Assistance Request
Content: A recon squad of the Arctic Route Union, while exploring a wrecked warship, has accidentally triggered its defense protocol. Certain members were wounded in this accident. Constructs are requested for assistance in disabling or destroying the warship's defense protocol.

Name: Medical Assistance Request
Content: The assault from the Corrupted has led to extensive damage to the bases and quite a number of casualties. Due to a manpower shortage, the Forsaken have requested the deployment of medic-type Constructs for critical care to the wounded.

Name: Ground Medical Assistance
Content: A squad of guards from a conservation area has gone missing after entering a nearby abandoned factory. Constructs skilled in exploration and rescue are requested for assistance.

Name: Artery to the Conservation Area Being Blocked
Content: The artery to a conservation area has been blocked by the Corrupted. To restore normal material transportation, Constructs are requested to clear the artery.

Name: Station Reconstruction Assistance
Content: The repair of the APUS is nearing completion, but the location for rebuilding its station is yet to be determined. To facilitate future goods transportation, Babylonia is requested to deploy Constructs to find an ideal location for the new station.

Name: Base Reconstruction Assistance
Content: The Forsaken have decided to rebuild a devastated base to resettle the refugees. Due to a manpower shortage, the Forsaken have requested Babylonia, with rewards offered, to arrange assistance in identifying a new location for the base.

Name: Desert Ruins Excavation
Content: Knowing that the Forsaken have discovered new desert ruins near an Oasis base, the WGAA wishes to explore the ruins together with the Forsaken. Constructs proficient in communication skills are requested to coordinate this ruins exploration between the two parties.

Name: Combat Reinforcements Request
Content: Asslam was ambushed by the Corrupted. As certain supplies were lost near the battle site, Babylonia is requested to eliminate Constructs to eliminate the Corrupted and retrieve the lost supplies.

Name: Combat Reinforcements Operation
Content: Enemies have appeared near a conservation area. The guards there are now engaging the enemies. Certain casualties have already been reported. Reinforcements are urgently requested.

Name: Settlement Construction Assistance
Content: A number of fishermen's seaside settlements were destroyed by the Corrupted from the sea. Babylonia is requested to deploy Constructs for assistance in rebuilding the settlements.

Name: Eliminate All Corrupted Around the Kowloong Ruins
Content: The results of the ruins exploration indicate that certain resources are retrievable in the Kowloong ruins. Babylonia is requested to deploy Constructs for assistance in eliminating all the Corrupted in the area and retrieving these resources.

Name: Military Exercise Guidance
Content: A new batch of graduates from military academies has arrived. Constructs are requested to assist in providing guidance for the new soldiers and commandants during a military exercise.

Name: Oasis Base Reconnaissance
Content: A recon team was ambushed by the Corrupted while scouting out a few locations reported to be ideal for building a base. Casualties have been confirmed. Due to a manpower shortage, the Oasis has requested Babylonia to send reinforcements.

Name: Emergency Nighter Maintenance
Content: The Nighter was attacked by unknown Hetero-Creatures that appeared on the sea surface, resulting in damage to certain devices. Babylonia is requested to provide assistance in investigating the abnormalities and repairing the damaged equipment.

Name: Ruins Abnormality Reconnaissance
Content: Abnormal waves have been detected in the depths of the Kowloong ruins. Due to technical and other constraints, Kowloong is currently unable to conduct an independent investigation. Therefore, Babylonia is requested to provide assistance for a cooperative investigation.

Name: Reconnaissance Assistance
Content: The Support Force is planning to establish a new goods transportation route on Earth, which requires Babylonia to provide assistance for preliminary reconnaissance and negotiation.

Name: Retrieval of Lost Materials
Content: A batch of the Engineering Force's materials was left on Earth because of an ambush by the Ascendant. A request has been made to fend off the Ascendant and retrieve the materials.

Name: Escort Diplomats
Content: Babylonia's diplomats are going to a conservation area on Earth for a diplomatic mission. Constructs are requested to provide an escort.

Name: Retrieval of Lost Materials
Content: Due to an attack by the Corrupted, the Support Force lost a batch of materials during transportation. Constructs are requested to head to the surface and retrieve the lost materials.

Name: Artifact Transportation Request
Content: The WGAA has again unearthed a batch of cultural and artistic artifacts. Constructs are requested to escort the transportation of these valuables back to Babylonia.

Name: Escort the Commerce Chamber Representative
Content: The Kowloong Chamber of Commerce plans to send a representative to visit Babylonia's conservation area on Earth. Babylonia is requested to provide an escort.

Name: Defecting Construct Reconnaissance
Content: Defecting Constructs have been spotted near a base. Casualties have been reported. Assistance in reconnaissance and pursuit is requested.

Name: Supplies Transportation Assistance
Content: While transporting a batch of supplies, the Support Force was attacked by the Corrupted. The transportation route is now inaccessible. Constructs with excellent combat and recon abilities are requested for assistance.

Name: Conservation Area Regular Reconnaissance
Content: Assistance is requested for regular reconnaissance of a conservation area's defense line and escorting a security squad.\nNote: This is a confidential mission that has to be handled with discretion.

Name: Eliminate the Corrupted
Content: A new site of ruins from the Golden Age was discovered on Earth. Constructs proficient in combat and reconnaissance are requested to eliminate the Corrupted occupying the ruins.\nNote: Constructs skilled in exploration are preferred in order to facilitate subsequent operations.

Name: Pursuit Defecting Constructs
Content: According to the preliminary recon report, the location of certain defecting Constructs has been identified. Their hideout is situated in complex terrain, making the operation more dangerous than usual. Combatants are requested for assistance in pursuit.

Name: Medical Engineering Guidance
Content: The special medical equipment aboard the Nighter and at the port is scheduled for an update. Babylonia is requested for assistance in addressing relevant medical equipment development issues.

Name: Joint Science Expedition
Content: Recently, both the science expedition around the Arctic Route Union and the joint exploration with the Arctic Route Union have made solid progress. Considering that some exploration points are located in areas abundant with sea ice, to facilitate subsequent exploration efforts, Babylonia is requested for assistance in the expedition work.

Name: Military Exchanges
Content: The Akdilek Commercial Alliance is currently planning a military exercise on Asslam, which will include combat and battlefield rescue drills. Babylonia has also been invited to participate by sending Constructs for the exercise.

Name: Oasis Transportation Paralyzed
Content: A horde of Corrupted has paralyzed the transportation to an Oasis base. Due to a manpower shortage, the Oasis has requested Babylonia, with rewards offered, to deploy Constructs to eliminate all the Corrupted in the area.

Name: Retrieval of Lost Materials
Content: A batch of materials critical to the Science Council was lost on the surface due to a raid by the Hetero-Creatures. Constructs are requested to eliminate the Corrupted and retrieve the materials.

Name: Kowloong Chamber of Commerce's Visit
Content: The KCC representative is going to visit Babylonia's conservation area on Earth. Babylonia is requested to provide an escort.\nGiven that the target location is situated in a region marked by multiple dangerous zones, outstanding combatants are strongly recommended.

Name: Dock Repair Assistance
Content: Due to an increase in the number of corrupted bionic sea animals, various docks of the Arctic Route Union have suffered severe damage. Babylonia is requested for assistance in repairing the docks and potential future cooperation.

Name: Protect the Defense Construction Site
Content: A defense construction site on Earth has suffered a certain extent of damage from an attack by a horde of abnormal Corrupted. Combatants with engineering knowledge are requested to eliminate the Corrupted and assist with repairing the construction site.

Name: Secure the Research Center Ruins
Content: It is likely that there is valuable data stored inside the research center. As many corrupted Constructs are still detectable inside the ruins, the Science Council has requested Constructs for assistance in eliminating all the threats there.

Name: Combat Medical Request
Content: A city on Earth has suffered a raid by the Corrupted. Medical support is requested as the medical devices there have been damaged. Given the potential for buildings in certain areas to collapse, the deployment of recon units is also recommended.

Name: Search for Survivors
Content: Incidents of structural collapse have occurred in the Kowloong ruins, leaving several individuals trapped and wounded. Babylonia is requested for assistance in a search and rescue operation.

Name: Reinforcements Exercise Guidance
Content: The F.O.S. Military Command College is planning to conduct a battlefield reinforcements exercise in the near future. This exercise will include battlefield reconnaissance, medical support, and more. Combatants with relevant skills are requested to provide guidance.

Name: Equipment Transportation
Content: A city on Earth has applied for a batch of new equipment, but the transportation route has been blocked by the Corrupted. Constructs with reconnaissance and engineering skills are requested to escort the transportation of this batch of equipment.

Name: Clean up the Research Center Ruins
Content: Recently, valuable data and materials have been discovered at a research center ruin site in the Antarctic Circle. An exploration operation is already scheduled. Babylonia is requested for assistance in the operation and the ensuing clear-up work.

Name: Queen's Visit
Content: Queen of Akdilek plans to visit a base of Babylonia. Babylonia is requested to provide escorts for her.

Name: Reconstruct the Kowloong Ruins
Content: The exploration team has discovered a Central Purification Filter in the Kowloong ruins. Plans are now underway to reconstruct the ruins into a peripheral base of Kowloong. Babylonia is requested to deploy Constructs for assistance in the excavation and reconstruction work.

Name: Conservation Area Routine Maintenance
Content: Routine maintenance of material and safety equipment in a conservation area is about to commence. Assistance is requested by the Engineering Force.

Name: Artifact Reclassification
Content: The recently retrieved artifacts and their associated reports have now arrived in Babylonia. Specialists with relevant expertise are requested to review and archive these reports.

Name: Medical Equipment Development
Content: In response to multiple reports of accidents during recon missions, the Star of Life plans to develop portable medical equipment specifically tailored for those missions. To ensure its suitability for recon units, specialists with relevant expertise are requested for its development.

Name: Reconstruct Conservation Area
Content: A conservation area on Earth has been savagely attacked, leaving major structural damage and heavy casualties. Constructs are requested to assist with the rescue operation and the ensuing reconstruction project.

Name: Medical Assistance Request
Content: An Arctic Route Union team encountered a structure collapse while retrieving data from a research center. Babylonia is requested to deploy Constructs for assistance in rescuing the wounded units.

Name: Exploration Equipment Transportation
Content: An application for exploration equipment, to be used for the ruins on Earth, has been approved, and the equipment is now ready for transportation. Constructs are requested to assist in eliminating all the threats along the transportation route.

Name: Resource Trade
Content: This season's resource trade is already underway. According to the trade agreement established between Babylonia and a few other organizations on Earth, a batch of resources, along with the associated funds, are ready for transportation. Assistance with the transportation and coordination work is hereby requested.

Name: Eliminate the Corrupted for Asslam
Content: Asslam was ambushed by the Corrupted while traveling through a region with a high concentration of the Punishing Virus. Babylonia is requested to deploy Constructs for assistance in eliminating the Corrupted.

Name: Golden Age Ruins
Content: Now that the ruins are secure, preparations for their exploration are proceeding as scheduled. The WGAA has submitted a proposal to the World Government for a joint construction project with the conservation areas surrounding the ruins. Constructs are requested to assist with both the exploration and the joint construction work.

Name: Conservation Area Reinforcements
Content: The Corrupted have been reported appearing in a conservation area on Earth. Specialists are requested to participate in a rescue operation with medical materials.

Name: Base Reconnaissance Request
Content: As the Oasis continues to take in more refugees, the capacity of its bases is nearing its limit. The Oasis plans to recover a base abandoned because of a raid by the Corrupted. Due to a manpower shortage, the Oasis has requested Babylonia to provide assistance in the recon operation.

Name: Medical Assistance Request
Content: An Oasis base has come under attack. Wounded refugees require evacuation and urgent treatment. Babylonia is requested to deploy Constructs with experience in rescue operations and piloting for assistance.

Name: Medical Assistance Request
Content: A WGAA archaeological Team was trapped during an inspection mission on Earth, with several members reported wounded. Medical assistance is requested. Those with serious injuries have to be admitted to the Star of Life headquarters. Constructs skilled in piloting are, therefore, also recommended for assistance.

Name: Combat Reinforcements Exercise
Content: The F.O.S. Military Command College is planning to conduct a battlefield reinforcements exercise in the near future. This exercise will include march route planning, material transportation, medical support, and more. Combatants with relevant skills are requested to provide guidance.

Name: Antarctic Circle Abnormality Reconnaissance
Content: Recently, frequent abnormalities have been detected under the sea ice in the Antarctic Circle. These are suspected to be associated with the atypical restlessness of the Corrupted. Constructs are requested to join an Arctic Route Union squad for a recon operation.

Name: Combat Medical Request
Content: A raid on City 126 has led to structural collapses with persons trapped within the debris. Combatants with recon skills are requested to assist with the medical and rescue operation.

Name: Pursuit Defecting Constructs
Content: A report has been received from a squad on Earth. They have located the hideout of the defecting Constructs, but several units were wounded during the pursuit. Reinforcements are requested.

Name: Routine Facility Maintenance
Content: This season's routine maintenance of the facilities in a conservation area is falling behind schedule. The Engineering Force is requested to deploy Constructs for assistance. As the conservation area is located in complicated terrain, possessing combat abilities is also highly recommended.

Name: The Kowloong Ruins Expedition
Content: A scientific research team from Kowloong encountered a number of Corrupted while exploring a ruins site at the border. Several members have been trapped in the ruins. Due to a lack of combatants in the team, Constructs proficient in combat and reconnaissance are requested to assist with the exploration work.

Name: Military Exchanges
Content: The Akdilek Commercial Alliance is currently planning a military exercise on Asslam. Babylonia has been invited to send Constructs with expertise in combat, reconnaissance, and piloting to attend the exercise.

Name: Excavate the Research Center Ruins
Content: Now that the research center is secure, the subsequent excavation operation will commence to retrieve research samples and test data.\nConstructs are requested to escort the Science Council's investigators and assist with the excavation operation.

Name: Support Route Reconnaissance
Content: To ensure a smoother support operation on Earth, the Support Force plans to establish a new support route. Constructs experienced in reconnaissance and engineering are requested to provide assistance.

Name: Protect Conservation Area
Content: A conservation area to the west of City 051 has been raided by a substantial number of enemies. They are now advancing toward a Scavenger's campsite. In addition to that, this incursion has sparked a violent conflict between the Scavengers and the conservation area. Combatants with strong negotiation skills are requested to eliminate the Corrupted and mediate this conflict.

Name: Assist with Conservation Area Reconstruction
Content: As the conservation area has been recovered, its reconstruction is set to commence shortly. Constructs are requested for assistance in this reconstruction project.

Name: Urgent Reinforcements to the Conservation Area
Content: The Corrupted have breached the defense line of a conservation area on Earth. Urgent reinforcements are requested.

Name: Eliminate All Threats in the Kowloong Ruins
Content: A scientific research team from Kowloong is preparing to initiate an investigation into a newly discovered ruins site. Due to technical and personnel constraints, the Kowloong Corp has requested Babylonia to join forces in eliminating the threats inside. All data retrieved will be shared between the research institutes of both parties.

Name: Urgent Treatment for Structural Collapses
Content: SOS! A station along a goods transportation route to Akdilek has collapsed. Babylonia is requested to deploy Constructs for assistance in the transportation of goods and the reconstruction of the station.

Name: Trade with Kowloong
Content: The Arctic Route Union and Kowloong are going to exchange a batch of goods. Due to the exceptional distance between the two ports, the Arctic Route Union has requested Babylonia, with rewards offered, to deploy Constructs as escorts to ensure smooth sailing.

Name: Goods Transshipment Notice
Content: A research center on Earth has hit a bottleneck and requires a batch of devices for further investigation. As the transportation route traverses multiple dangerous regions, Babylonia is requested to deploy Constructs to escort the goods transportation.

Name: Ruins Reconstruction
Content: Recently, a new ruins site has been discovered in the Arctic Route Union region. Preliminary analysis indicates that it is possible to rebuild the ruins into a base.\nAs the reconstruction is planned to be conducted jointly by Babylonia and the Arctic Route Union, Constructs are requested to undertake missions in the designated region.

Name: Reinforcements to Abnormal Conservation Area
Content: Connection with a conservation area on Earth has been abruptly severed, and abnormal activities of the Hetero-Creatures have been identified around it. Constructs are requested to refortify the defense facilities in the conservation area and stand by for any urgent situations.

Name: Reinforcements to the Nighter
Content: A horde of Corrupted has raided a pier where the Nighter was docked, resulting in heavy civilian casualties. Given the Nighter's lack of medical resources, Babylonia is requested to deploy Constructs for assistance in both the rescue operation and the subsequent reconstruction of the pier.

Name: Pursuit Defecting Constructs
Content: Note: Reports indicate that the defecting Constructs have invaded a conservation area, posting a threat to the civilians inside. Scout- and support-type Constructs are requested for assistance in tracking down the defecting Constructs and protecting the civilians.

Name: Ruins Refortification Project
Content: The WGAA has discovered a ruins site on Earth. Preliminary investigation reveals that it is of significant human cultural value. However, its fragile structure is at risk of imminent collapse.\nAfter acquiring enough materials, the WGAA has requested the deployment of Constructs for assistance in transporting the materials for the refortification project.

Name: Base Reconstruction Assistance
Content: With the activities of the Corrupted at the Arctic Route Union border subsiding, it is an opportunity to rebuild the damaged bases in that region. Babylonia is requested to deploy specialists with relevant expertise to provide technical guidance for the reconstruction.

Name: Sample Collection and Transportation
Content: For some of the Science Council's projects to proceed to the next phase, they require samples collected from hazardous regions on Earth. Constructs proficient in reconnaissance and piloting are requested to provide assistance for this task.

Name: Underground Ruins Investigation
Content: A new underground ruins site has been discovered near a recently built station, but the investigation has hardly made progress due to the site's complicated terrain. To explore its internal structure, Babylonia is requested to deploy Constructs for assistance. The investigation results will be shared mutually.

Name: Negotiation With Scavengers
Content: A group of Scavengers, who had initially claimed that they only intended to collect materials, turned out to have damaged a conservation area's defense facilities, stolen its materials, and even wounded several of its officers. Constructs are requested to defuse the conflicts and assist with repairing the damaged defense facilities.

Name: Base Facility Upgrade
Content: Because of the vulnerability of its defense facilities, the Oasis has sustained significant losses from attacks by the Corrupted. It has requested Babylonia to deploy Constructs for assistance in refortifying its defenses. In return, the Forsaken will support Babylonia's future goods transportation and exchange.

Name: Protect Oasis Base
Content: An Oasis base has come under attack by a large number of Corrupted. Its defenses are already on the brink of collapse. Immediate assistance is required to evacuate the refugees and rescue the injured.

Name: Casualty Evacuation Request
Content: The casualties in an Oasis base have exceeded its capacity. The Oasis is planning to send the lightly injured to another base and has requested assistance in transportation.

Name: Combat Reinforcements Request
Content: A patrolling squad was ambushed in the Antarctic Circle. With their vehicles damaged and no specialists in rescue and combat at the nearby campsites, they are now unable to return to their base. Babylonia is requested to deploy Constructs for assistance.

Name: Eliminate the Corrupted
Content: A train was ambushed by the Hetero-Creatures while traveling through a region with a high concentration of the Punishing Virus. During the ambush, a number of Corrupted managed to intrude into the train. Babylonia is requested to deploy combatants to eliminate the remaining Corrupted with Akdilek.

Name: Structural Collapses at Construction Sites
Content: Emergency: An earthquake has caused structural collapses with several casualties at construction sites in multiple conservation areas. Babylonia is requested to deploy Constructs for a rescue and reconstruction mission.

Name: Abnormal Conservation Area Investigation
Content: Babylonia has detected abnormal activities in a conservation area on Earth. Unable to contact the conservation area, Babylonia has requested Constructs to investigate the situation and prepare for potential rescue and evacuation of civilians.

Name: Negotiation Commission from the Nighter
Content: A vessel carrying a batch of supplies for the Nighter has been forcibly hijacked by a group of thugs. As the vessel is far from where the Nighter is currently docked and close to Babylonia's conservation area, Babylonia is requested to deploy Constructs for assistance in negotiations to release the vessel.

Name: Combat Medical Request
Content: A battle on the defense line of a conservation area on Earth has successfully driven out the Hetero-Creatures, but the casualties were greater than expected. Medical assistance is requested for the transportation of the injured and the repair of damaged buildings.

Name: Medical Supplies Transportation
Content: A defense line on Earth is in the brink of collapse and direly needs medical supplies. The supplies are ready for transportation. Constructs are requested to provide assistance.

Name: Medical Assistance
Content: Due to the continuous shifting of quicksand, a number of Oasis bases have been destroyed, and numerous civilians have been trapped in a dangerous quicksand zone where casualties have already occurred. As the Forsaken lacks sufficient manpower to save all trapped civilians, Babylonia is requested to provide assistance in the rescue operations.

Name: >>>System Activation
Content: Before Activating the Commission System—\nPlease note that this system, developed by Babylonia, will automatically issue missions that do not require a commandant's support to Constructs.\n>>>Please accept this commission to activate the system.

Name: Help Me Reclassify Documents
Content: Mr. Asimov told me to "find a person or two who understand what confidentiality is to help reclassify the documents about the special materials from the last experiment." It's certain that Mr. Asimov has remembered all the important data, but... but the normally confidential things should still be properly archived, right?\nMr. Asimov, am... am I doing this correctly?

Name: Artworks Reclassification
Content: While the artworks from Earth have been piling up in the WGAA's warehouse, most of our manpower is still concentrated on exploring new ruins on Earth.\nPlease send assistants used to handling confidential materials to help reclassify our artworks. After all, no one can guarantee that they don't hold any other secrets.\n—Allen

Name: Please Bring Our Captain Back
Content: ...Always the first one arriving on the scene when it comes to repairing engines or demolishing abandoned buildings...\nPlease bring her back from the engine repair site and check on the broken engine. If we let her do it on her own... I don't want to see an explosion and become a piece of space debris with her.\n—Teddy

Name: Hey, Care to Lend a Hand?
Content:
This shipment of supplies needs to be delivered to the Forsaken, but the Supply Force is stretched, and the Forsaken does not have the people to collect it.
Watanabe seems embarrassed to ask for Babylonia's help. That said, how can we turn away when what is left of humanity is in need of help?
Let me issue this commission, and to the commandant willing to accept this, I really appreciate it.
—Bridget

Name: Purify Conservation Area 019
Content:
A new group of Corrupted has been sighted near Conservation Area 019. Please eliminate them.
Please be aware the movement path and origin of these Corrupted are still unknown. Constructs with recon abilities are recommended.
Most squads are already on a mission recently, so I have posted this message in the commission system. Whoever takes it must still treat it seriously.
—Celica

Name: Camouflage Skills Needed
Content:
We suspect there are defect Constructs within the Conservation Area, and need someone with good camouflage skills to assist the initial investigation.
Participants must accept a certain level of modification to their Coatings as they need to disguise as normal Constructs and civilians.
And... What else to add?
Whatever. I'll explain once you are here.
—Purifying Force Member

Name: Hmm... I Need This, and...
Content:
Ahem... How should I write this? Two Constructs with outstanding communication skills are needed in the Conservation Area. We urgently need construction materials and would like to get them from Akdilek Commercial Alliance via exchange.
Let me see... Parts and wrenches of special models, as well as...
I don't think you can remember. Better write them all down.
Those with a * sign next to them are the most urgently needed. Try to get them from Akdilek first. If the quoted prices are different, just keep a receipt and the Engineering Force will pay the gap. If you really cannot get these parts, we will have to wait for Babylonia then.
—Karenina

Name: A Blocked Road?!
Content:
[A noisy recording that sounds like Bridget's voice]

What's going on? I thought this road was fixed—mudflow and earthquakes? What about my cargo? It's supposed to go to the Conservation Area!
I hope commandants who have received this request can send Constructs for emergency support or transport, as the cargo contains medicines that are urgently needed in the Conservation Area. We don't have much time. Please send reinforcements ASAP—

Name: Constellia Maintenance
Content: Hi, this is Ayla from WGAA!\nBabylonia has officially taken over Constellia. WGAA is running an initial inspection on this city and we realize that some aged facilities need maintenance. While WGAA has specialists who are capable of this task, Constellia is just too big for us to handle alone.\nIf you have the required skills, feel free to let us know. WGAA is offering great rewards!

Name: Bring Back Emergency Specimen
Content:
[A short recording that sounds like Asimov's voice]

The specimen and report should be on my desk THREE DAYS AGO. Who can tell me why I still have not got them?
...Mudflow? Earthquake? I don't need excuses. I just want the specimen and report. What about the commission system? Why don't we use it to hire Constructs to bring them over?
(The recording ends with some noises. Something seems to have been knocked off the desk in panic...)

Name: Reinforcements Needed in Conservation Area
Content: Mudflow had blocked the main road to that Conversation Area. We only received an incomplete message from the surface. We urgently request the assistance of Constructs and the Star of Life together.\n[Vague Recording]\n—Mudflow! We must hurry... Medicines... Sick... Danger...

Name: New Medical Areas
Content: A new batch of medical supplies has been approved. We plan to establish some medical areas in the Conservation Areas near the Danger Zone so those in need can be treated ASAP. Help us bring the supplies to the target locations if you have time.\nBy the way, I also requested a number of large transport vehicles... Just leave a few in the underground of each of the new medical area.\nSome things should only happen once and never again.

Name: Damaged Road
Content: Um... Hello? Hello? Is this how I'm supposed to use it? Such an old terminal...\nAhem, here's the thing. A group of overloaded vehicles recently drove over a road we just paved and damaged it. We have no idea where they came from, but we are really short-handed at the moment. Boss said we could post a request here to ask you for help...\nRest assured that we will pay a reasonable fee for your service. That's all.

Name: Hello? This is...
Content: ...Hello there? This is Lisa from the Arctic Route Union. I run a fur shop and would like you to help deliver a shipment of fur to me. The forest has not been safe lately and a lot of strange creatures are lurking inside. On top of a reasonable fee, I will also provide some high-quality fur.\nActually, Rosetta told me about this service. Could you please send her if possible? It's been a long time since I last met her...

Name: Akdilek's Exchange Request
Content:
The reconstruction of Asslam is under way, which means we will be staying in the same location for the time to come.
As Akdilek IV, I'd like to take this opportunity to propose an exchange event between Babylonia Constructs and Akdilek Commercial Alliance (ACA).
Asslam has been running for too long and needs a break. I hope our young people have a chance to see the outside world with their own eyes.
We will offer the corresponding "rewards" for your time and effort. Below is a list of items for trade.
—Akdilek Jamilah

Name: Settlement Points
Content: The Nighter plans to establish a few settlement points near the shore around Kowloong City in order to accommodate residents returning from the Nighter. However, we are short-handed due to the severe damage in Kowloong City, so we hope to borrow some manpower from Babylonia to help us look for some livable locations. We will arrange for supplies from nearby areas, so don't worry about that...\nHey, is this how I'm supposed to post the request? Pulao? Why are you standing so far away?! Come take a look!\nThis is still your terminal no matter how far you are!

Name: Application for Regular Joint Exploration
Content:
RE: A Formal Application for Joint Exploration
They told me to fill out an application before they could send more people down to explore these ruins together. Is this the correct report?
Kowloong Corp would like to hereby apply for a joint exploration with Babylonia of the Golden Age ruins near the Conservation Area of Babylonia and the border of Kowloong City. All the information and data retrieved from the exploration will be shared across both parties.
Will that suffice? Hurry, time is running out!

Name: Teach Them a Lesson!
Content:
Kids nowadays really don't know their place. A few days ago, I caught a few who sneaked into the shuttle. They insisted on going to the surface for drills, so they could help the Constructs!
Fine, I shall show them what real Constructs look like! Constructs who can defeat the Corrupted!
I need a few good ones to teach them a lesson...
Actually, please hold back your power. Just let them feel the pain without breaking their bones.
It's not really a bad thing when they demonstrate such a level of enthusiasm...

Name: Ugh... So Many Documents...
Content:
Ah... Why am I getting so many reports again? Deployments, self-reflections, surveillance observations, abnormal Hetero-Creature activities...
Every end of the month, these reports just pile up. How am I supposed to finish them all by myself?!
Sigh... Can someone help me to at least categorize them? I'll make coffee for you for one week.
—Celica

Name: Help! Can Someone Lend a Hand?
Content:
First of all... Don't be scared, we are not asking you to do missions for us.
Previously, we sent out some surveys, because the HQ said the Purifying Force was too aggressive and we should look for clues with "more peaceful and gentle" methods...
Anyway, the surveys are now back but we don't have anyone who can classify and analyze them... Ahem, can someone help us to sort out the surveys? Much appreciated!
—Purifying Force Member

Name: Can Someone Help Us to Station Here?
Content: The reconstruction of the conservation area is an enormous project... I not only have to stop the annoying Corrupted from disturbing the construction, but also have to keep an eye on Karenina so she doesn't run around telling others their living place will be demolished immediately...\nCan someone help us here? Otherwise, it's only a matter of time before I blow up Karenina, her Blast Hammer, as well as this conservation area.\n—Teddy

Name: Hey! Good Morning!
Content:
Yo, did you take the bait? If you have time, could you help me organize the recent documents of Support Force into categories?
I have no idea how they pile up so fast. Celica's been chasing me for them, but most of us are on surface missions. So... Thanks in advance!
I'll thank you in person once I'm back!
—Bridget

Name: Assist Needed for Reconstruction of Constellia
Content:
Greetings, the commandant who has accepted this request.
With Ayla as the leader, some WGAA members have joined forces with the Engineering Force to enter Constellia. We plan to rebuild this amazing city in different stages, but some colleagues still have other commitments and may not be able to meet the original deadlines.
If time permits, could you please assign some Constructs to assist in the reconstruction of Constellia? Rest assured that you will be well rewarded. We look forward to hearing from you.
—Allen

Name: Investigate the Deserted Research Center
Content: Mr. Asimov said they found a deserted research center in the surface conservation area. He, um, would like someone to help bring back some data that he needs, because... Um... Because "the fools at the conservation area will never figure out which data I need, and which I don't. Stop sending me the foreign-language menus in the research center! I don't give a thing about what they ate."\nUm... Mr. Asimov... Do we really have to put it like that...?\n—Rosa

Name: Emergency! We Found...
Content: The Oasis seems to be hiding something from us, and we have no idea what's going on... Actually, everyone looks a little strange recently. Watanabe once told us we could trust the Gray Raven Commandant in Babylonia, so I'm sending this to you now...\nI hope this old terminal can still deliver this message to Babylonia. Just what is going on—\n—Anonymous Member

Name: A Great Number of Corrupted Have Appeared
Content: The Arctic Route Union was struck by an unexpected Hetero-Creature attack. Some of our outer bases were already lost. The Forest Guards are doing their best, but the enemies are outnumbering them. We hope Babylonia can send Constructs to protect the port and city along with Forest Guards.\n—Diana

Name: Very Important!
Content:
Wow, this is my first time using a Babylonia terminal. Feels so cool!
Alright, I have a big business opportunity for you. Ahem! We have already secured some funding for the reconstruction of some damaged outposts near the rail. Part of the construction materials are already in place, but we still need manpower.
I would really appreciate if someone can come down to help us. Rest assured that your hard work will be rewarded!
—Changyu

Name: The Nighter's Invitation to Collaborated Reconstruction
Content: The reconstruction of the Nighter's ground outpost will be commencing soon. We have prepared a banquet, and would like to invite Babylonia for a cornerstone ceremony, followed by discussions of further details regarding the project.\n—Chaofeng

Name: Merchant Routes with Kowloong
Content: Kowloong plans to engage in trading activities with Babylonia's surrounding outposts, but some of the routes are currently occupied by Corrupted. We hope Babylonia can assist us to clear these routes.\n—Bai Gui

Name: Whoa!
Content: OMG! Can't believe I can actually post a request with this terminal I just found! I-I'm gonna ask Gray Raven Commandant to host a seminar in the college! Posting... Success! Hooray, I can finally meet my idol!\n—F.O.S. Student A
